# Table layout & icon rules (titan-compositions)

## Cell and header alignment (mandatory)

- **`th` and `td` default:** `text-align: left` for all copy, numbers, and mixed content (text + icon, avatar + label, etc.).
- **`text-align: center` ONLY** when the cell contains **exclusively** one of:
  - a **decorative / informational icon** (no text beside it),
  - an **avatar alone** (no name or secondary text in the same cell),
  - a **checkbox** (use `table-col-checkbox` / `table-cell-checkbox`),
  - a **drag handle** (use `table-col-drag` / `table-cell-drag`),
  - a **single action icon** (e.g. kebab column: `table-col-actions` / `table-cell-actions`).
- For **avatar-only** or **icon-only** columns, use classes `table-col-avatar-only` / `table-cell-avatar-only` or `table-col-icon-only` / `table-cell-icon-only` (see `titan-compositions.css`), or `th.table-align-center` / `td.table-align-center` when appropriate.
- Do **not** center normal data columns for aesthetics.

## Cell icons (tbody)

- Icons inside table body cells (`<td>`) are **always decorative/informational** — never interactive buttons.
- They must be plain SVGs without hover or pressed states (no `icon-ghost`, no `icon-secondary`).
- Size: `--icon-size-m` (16px) with `stroke-width: var(--icon-stroke-m)` (1.5) — matching the navbar icon dimensions.
- The CSS rule `.table-borderless tbody td svg` enforces this globally.
- If a cell needs an actionable icon (e.g. kebab menu), wrap it in a `<Button className="icon-base">` — the basic icon button with no bg on any state.

## Header icons (thead)

- Sort arrows and info icons use `--icon-size-s` (12px) with `stroke-width: var(--icon-stroke-s)` (1.25).
- Sort icons are inside `.column-sort-icon` spans; info icons get `className="column-header-info-icon"` directly on the `<svg>`.
- Both wrappers (`.column-sort-icon-wrap`, `.column-header-info-wrap`) use identical `width/height: var(--icon-size-s)`.

## Action columns

- The actions column uses `icon-base` (basic icon button) for triggers — transparent bg, no hover/pressed bg, only color change.
- Never use `icon-ghost` or `icon-secondary` for table row actions.
